- The entire setting should change:
The website should have two modes - authenticated and non-authenticated.
In the non-authenticated mode, users can only view the results and the guesses of other users in other brackets.
In the authenticated mode, users can make their own guesses, view their own guess history, and access the admin panel if they have admin privileges.
Tournament structure should be defined in a way that allows for easy updates and changes, such as adding or removing teams, changing the tournament format, etc.
This can be achieved by creating a flexible data model for the tournament and implementing an admin interface for managing it.
The tournament should have stages, games, and teams as separate entities, with clear relationships between them.
The guessing system should be designed to allow for different types of guesses, such as predicting the winner, predicting the exact score, etc.


